<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Bobby:
[I]Say is there something like camouflage going to be in the game? Greenish creatures lurking in the grass, brown creatures next to trees etc. that try to prey on the character once he’s close enough, or once he’s standing say in the middle of a bunch of unsuspecting trees. Also, creatures won’t try to leave their natural habitat, e.g. the greenish creatures won’t try to leave the grass they are on.
Also skeletons might use “camouflage” to their advantage by being stuck to walls or lying on the ground, while the player thinks that they might be some poor prisoners or adventurers who have died long ago (here again there is the chance of surrounding the player character by getting up (maybe even getting assembled in the process from a pile of bones) or coming off the walls), or using the skeletons as messengers (or the one to pull the lever) and what not).

Are all usually enemy creatures going be hostile or are there going to be a couple who will just ignore you (e.g. two skeletons talking to each other about the good old days while staying chained to a wall or walking past you as if you weren't there, or how about a civilization of autonomos “spooky” skeletons) or even be friendly towards you (who turn hostile if the player attacks them (and gets zero exp. in the process), or turn hostile cause they were playing friendly)?

Are there going to be hostile creatures that don’t attack the player immediately, but wait for him to make the first move (such as come closer or attack or talk)?

Are intelligent creatures going to be able to use items the player is allowed to (such as using healing or mana potions; although I don’t think e.g. skeletons could use that)?

Are intelligent creatures going to be able to pick things up from the ground, tables, chests?

Are there going to be “bait” NPCs or creatures? E.g. someone follows you or watches you closely and when you try to approach it, it runs away, while e.g. the player runs after it, just to land into a trap (e.g. it has company on the other end). Maybe the player doesn’t just approach it, but tries to silently follow it while it goes somewhere, again just to be lead into a trap.

[This message has been edited by Bobby (edited 20-12-1999).][/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
